00:57.934 --> 00:59.814
DARCY: <i>It wasn't meant to
be this way. You know?</i>

01:04.732 --> 01:05.984
We make our plans, sure.

01:07.235 --> 01:08.486
But life...

01:10.488 --> 01:12.365
Life is what happens
to you along the way.

01:16.661 --> 01:18.204
You know, at first,
I didn't want this.

01:19.289 --> 01:20.498
I didn't want to connect.

01:20.707 --> 01:21.907
I didn't want to get involved.

01:22.709 --> 01:24.085
And she kept on at me.

01:25.420 --> 01:28.172
"This is what life is. This is
why we're here, to connect."

01:29.757 --> 01:30.758
"To build."

01:33.636 --> 01:35.179
We're here to build something.

01:39.434 --> 01:40.935
And then we had Theo.

01:42.145 --> 01:45.148
And then I understood
that she was right.

01:48.776 --> 01:50.612
We're not meant to be alone.

01:56.159 --> 01:57.702
You know what she said to me?

01:58.286 --> 02:00.204
She said that even
the most damaged heart

02:01.873 --> 02:03.166
can be mended.

02:05.668 --> 02:07.712
Even the most damaged heart.

02:35.531 --> 02:36.949
(CELL PHONE VIBRATING)

02:40.078 --> 02:41.204
Yeah.

02:42.789 --> 02:44.415
No, I'm with Vic.

02:45.083 --> 02:46.084
What?

02:46.250 --> 02:47.251
(POUNDING ON DOOR)

02:49.837 --> 02:51.477
I can't let you in
until Alphonse is home.

02:51.506 --> 02:53.007
Alphonse is on his way.

02:53.091 --> 02:54.384
Where?

02:54.509 --> 02:55.760
In the basement.

03:08.439 --> 03:09.440
Oh, Paulie.

03:11.025 --> 03:12.068
No.

03:30.962 --> 03:32.296
DARCY: It's Paul.

03:37.969 --> 03:38.970
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

03:39.053 --> 03:40.722
Why is the alarm off?

03:40.805 --> 03:43.933
I told you that you
should always have it on!

03:44.642 --> 03:45.727
(WOMAN SPEAKING SPANISH)

03:45.810 --> 03:47.687
She said that she
didn't turn it off.

03:48.312 --> 03:49.313
Go.

04:19.427 --> 04:21.721
"719, now you realize."

04:21.803 --> 04:22.805
What?

05:01.052 --> 05:03.596
DARCY: What the fuck?
This shit is crazy.

05:03.846 --> 05:05.223
Now he's killing us.

05:05.681 --> 05:06.849
Call the locksmith.

05:07.350 --> 05:09.727
And get that asshole from the
alarm company over here.

05:14.482 --> 05:16.150
"Now you realize."

05:43.928 --> 05:45.429
(SIGHS) I know who's
doing this to me.

05:46.347 --> 05:48.432
(<i>FREAK</i> PLAYING)

06:20.339 --> 06:22.049
(MOANING)

06:33.102 --> 06:34.937
(BANGING ON WALL)

06:38.733 --> 06:39.734
Killed for less.

06:43.112 --> 06:44.780
A little uncouth to
come without a call.

06:45.948 --> 06:47.388
There's a better
place for you to be.

06:47.742 --> 06:48.910
Get out. Go.

06:48.993 --> 06:50.745
Am I gonna get paid?

07:01.505 --> 07:02.882
Have you seen this man?

07:03.925 --> 07:05.760
Paul? Everyone
knows Paul's missing.

07:06.093 --> 07:07.845
I want you to think
before you answer.

07:08.429 --> 07:09.680
'Cause I'm getting
to the bottom of this.

07:09.847 --> 07:11.140
The bottom of what?

07:11.349 --> 07:12.975
Three months of letters.

07:13.935 --> 07:15.478
Three months of torment.

07:16.103 --> 07:18.356
Not being able to leave
my house without wondering

07:18.439 --> 07:22.193
if some coward is gonna
sneak up behind me and...

07:24.528 --> 07:25.696
Paul was looking into this.

07:25.821 --> 07:28.157
And I think he found exactly
what he was looking for.

07:28.491 --> 07:30.660
But before he
could come and tell me,

07:31.327 --> 07:35.498
my friend Paul shows up
strangled in my freezer.

07:36.207 --> 07:38.834
You've got a lot of enemies,
don't you, Alphonse?

07:41.879 --> 07:44.423
Three months ago you and
I had our disagreement!

07:44.507 --> 07:46.676
I raised my take to 25%

07:46.926 --> 07:49.720
to allow you to continue
to operate in my buildings.

07:49.971 --> 07:51.889
I started getting letters
three months ago!

07:52.056 --> 07:53.683
That's no fucking coincidence!

07:53.766 --> 07:54.934
That's not fucking accurate!

07:55.017 --> 07:58.479
You asked for 30%, and Lon told
you, you could only ask me for 20%.

07:58.896 --> 08:01.983
So if anyone was bent out of shape,
it was fucking you, Alphonse.

08:02.233 --> 08:03.734
Who's in this picture?

08:04.568 --> 08:06.153
I don't fucking know. Who the
fuck is in this picture?

08:06.237 --> 08:07.238
I don't know!

08:10.074 --> 08:12.034
What am I supposed to realize?

08:12.410 --> 08:15.871
What does 719 mean? What am
I going to fucking realize?

08:15.955 --> 08:17.790
What am I gonna
fucking realize?

08:18.249 --> 08:20.251
Darcy, want to give me
a hand here, mate?

08:20.418 --> 08:23.254
He ain't got shit
to do with this!

08:23.379 --> 08:25.423
I've been picking up from
Harry for over a year.

08:25.506 --> 08:27.925
No. He's a fucking liar
so you shut the fuck up.

08:28.551 --> 08:30.712
I'm gonna ask you again.
What am I supposed to realize?

08:33.264 --> 08:35.265
I don't care what you
think I've done to you,

08:35.850 --> 08:38.102
you are not sanctioned
to kill me.

08:38.184 --> 08:39.895
That much I do fucking know.

08:40.938 --> 08:42.378
So it's not on,
you even coming here!

08:42.898 --> 08:43.982
"Not on"?

08:46.360 --> 08:48.195
The term is, "Not cool."

08:49.613 --> 08:51.774
It's you fucking English.
You always do shit like that.

08:51.991 --> 08:53.451
Alphonse, just...

08:57.079 --> 08:58.289
Well...

09:00.916 --> 09:03.461
You also make your
sevens like this.

09:19.060 --> 09:20.061
You

09:20.978 --> 09:22.772
are not sanctioned

09:23.731 --> 09:25.024
to kill me.

09:28.152 --> 09:29.153
Fuck it.

09:31.155 --> 09:32.990
(<i>FREAK</i> CONTINUES PLAYING)

09:46.837 --> 09:47.838
(GROANS)

09:54.178 --> 09:55.179
(GUN CLICKS)

10:30.256 --> 10:31.715
What the fuck
y'all waiting for?

10:31.966 --> 10:33.008
Do it.

10:36.554 --> 10:37.680
(GROANS)

10:40.224 --> 10:41.350
(GROANING)

10:55.364 --> 10:56.323
Fuck, you've been hit.

10:56.407 --> 10:57.408
Don't worry about it.

10:58.492 --> 10:59.994
(PANTING)

11:48.000 --> 11:49.168
(METALLIC CLATTERING)

11:50.419 --> 11:51.879
DOCTOR: A bit better
this time.

11:53.964 --> 11:55.090
(SOBS)

11:57.635 --> 12:00.075
NURSE: Will you be all right to
drive yourself home, Beatrice?

12:27.623 --> 12:29.333
(VACUUM WHIRRING)

12:35.673 --> 12:36.924
(VACUUM STOPS)

13:15.296 --> 13:16.297
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

13:16.380 --> 13:18.424
Why don't you go over and
introduce yourself to him?

13:18.507 --> 13:20.217
Oh, Mom.
What are you doing?

13:20.676 --> 13:22.469
You're supposed to
lie down and relax.

13:22.553 --> 13:23.554
Huh?

13:31.812 --> 13:32.813
(SIGHS)

13:33.188 --> 13:36.650
I was relaxing so much
I saw a white light.

13:36.734 --> 13:37.776
(LAUGHS)

13:37.860 --> 13:40.070
Well, if you see it again,
don't walk into it.

13:40.404 --> 13:43.115
I still have a lot of things to
take out on you for my childhood.

13:43.198 --> 13:44.408
(CHUCKLES)

13:45.409 --> 13:46.410
It's beautiful.

13:46.660 --> 13:48.454
I love the color.
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

13:48.537 --> 13:49.663
Me too.

13:49.747 --> 13:51.290
It's very pretty.

13:51.373 --> 13:52.916
I'll run your bath.

13:53.459 --> 13:54.668
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

13:54.752 --> 13:57.338
You don't stop looking at him.
You should ask him out.

13:57.463 --> 13:58.547
Go out.

13:58.630 --> 13:59.673
Live your life.

14:00.924 --> 14:03.135
You're alive, after all.

14:03.802 --> 14:05.637
(BATH WATER RUNNING)

15:10.994 --> 15:11.995
(CELL PHONE RINGS)

15:15.999 --> 15:17.334
Hello?

15:19.670 --> 15:20.838
Hello?

15:24.967 --> 15:26.176
I got your note.

15:30.514 --> 15:31.515
Hi.

15:31.849 --> 15:33.600
Uh...

15:36.311 --> 15:37.312
VICTOR: <i>Hi.</i>

15:37.604 --> 15:38.647
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

15:38.730 --> 15:40.482
Go out.

15:40.566 --> 15:42.526
Go out on the balcony.

15:48.031 --> 15:49.491
I...

15:51.702 --> 15:53.537
I wasn't sure you got it.

15:54.371 --> 15:56.540
I was wondering if I
put it in the wrong box?

15:56.874 --> 15:57.875
No.

15:58.959 --> 16:00.461
No. It's mine.

16:10.137 --> 16:11.138
So...

16:12.598 --> 16:13.891
The note.

16:16.643 --> 16:18.854
I just thought since we...

16:21.356 --> 16:24.526
I thought it would be
nice to finally meet you.

16:31.241 --> 16:32.367
Beatrice.

16:36.288 --> 16:37.498
Victor.

16:48.926 --> 16:50.594
(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

16:52.221 --> 16:53.222
No, thanks.

17:09.195 --> 17:10.405
You don't talk a lot.

17:12.532 --> 17:13.992
Not much, no.

17:16.328 --> 17:17.663
It's okay.

17:18.038 --> 17:19.373
I talk enough for both of us.

17:19.540 --> 17:20.624
(CHUCKLES)

17:20.707 --> 17:23.167
I talk too much.
Everybody says so.

17:28.382 --> 17:29.466
Um...

17:29.758 --> 17:30.759
You speak French?

17:32.761 --> 17:33.804
I'd like to.

17:33.887 --> 17:35.347
Yeah?
Sure.

17:37.307 --> 17:38.308
Another language?

17:39.768 --> 17:41.103
Hungarian.

17:42.312 --> 17:43.939
You're Hungarian?

17:46.441 --> 17:47.693
You don't have an accent.

17:49.319 --> 17:50.988
I worked very hard
to get rid of it.

17:55.450 --> 17:56.451
So...

17:58.745 --> 17:59.746
A job?

18:01.331 --> 18:02.457
I'm...

18:04.334 --> 18:06.336
Right now I'm
dabbling in real estate.

18:07.045 --> 18:10.424
The people I work for, they buy
buildings in need of renovations.

18:10.757 --> 18:12.676
Fix them up and run them.

18:13.719 --> 18:14.720
Hmm.

18:22.060 --> 18:23.353
(EXHALES SOFTLY)

18:32.696 --> 18:34.281
You? A job?

18:36.325 --> 18:37.326
Yeah.

18:39.953 --> 18:42.706
I was involved in
a car accident last year.

18:43.415 --> 18:45.042
I was a beautician before.

18:48.086 --> 18:50.213
They rebuilt part of my face.

18:52.424 --> 18:55.302
But it's kind of hard
to give advice on beauty now.

18:56.136 --> 18:57.429
And...

18:58.388 --> 19:00.390
I have to smile
a lot in my job.

19:00.682 --> 19:03.060
Most of the time,
it hurts to smile.

19:08.523 --> 19:10.984
I don't get to smile
so much in my work.

19:11.193 --> 19:12.361
No?
No.

19:12.819 --> 19:14.613
Maybe you and I should switch jobs.
Yeah.

19:18.116 --> 19:19.242
So, what else?

19:22.579 --> 19:24.122
I swear sometimes.

19:24.414 --> 19:25.540
Especially when I drink.

19:25.624 --> 19:26.625
Me too.

19:27.793 --> 19:28.794
Fuck.

19:30.087 --> 19:31.088
Shit.

19:32.339 --> 19:33.632
(LAUGHING)

19:34.883 --> 19:36.802
Careful. You're smiling.

19:43.433 --> 19:44.851
Tonight it's worth it.

19:56.655 --> 19:58.699
I want to take you somewhere.

19:58.865 --> 19:59.991
(LAUGHS)

20:00.450 --> 20:01.618
So where are we going?

20:02.119 --> 20:03.370
Are we going to a club?

20:03.954 --> 20:04.955
No.

20:05.038 --> 20:06.456
No?
Very cold.

20:06.790 --> 20:07.791
Very cold.
Yeah.

20:07.874 --> 20:08.875
All right.

20:09.292 --> 20:11.795
Well, then are
we going to a park?

20:12.129 --> 20:13.547
Hmm... (LAUGHS)

20:14.297 --> 20:15.298
Warmer.

20:21.263 --> 20:22.681
I thought you talk a lot?

20:23.432 --> 20:24.766
I thought you don't.

20:24.975 --> 20:26.455
Must be the company.
Usually, I don't.

20:32.941 --> 20:34.151
You can turn here.

20:37.195 --> 20:38.530
Pull over. Just there.

20:53.128 --> 20:57.299
You're afraid I'll think you came
tonight because you felt sorry for me.

20:58.675 --> 21:00.594
You don't have to
play these games, Victor.

21:01.344 --> 21:03.013
I know why you really came.

21:04.347 --> 21:06.057
You're just being careful.

21:06.808 --> 21:10.645
You want to find out if the girl who's
been watching you saw what you did.

21:14.858 --> 21:17.986
I saw you kill this man.

21:34.920 --> 21:36.797
I saw you strangle him.

21:37.380 --> 21:38.632
I saw you take him away.

21:39.674 --> 21:42.219
Now you're trying to clean up a
mess that cannot be cleaned up.

21:44.095 --> 21:45.555
But, I...

21:46.181 --> 21:48.475
I think your secret
will be safe with me.

21:53.021 --> 21:54.397
This is the man

21:54.731 --> 21:56.650
who hit my car
when he was drunk.

22:01.530 --> 22:03.073
This is the man
who did this to me.

22:04.866 --> 22:06.034
I want you to kill him.

22:08.662 --> 22:10.539
As you did with
the man in your apartment.

22:11.164 --> 22:12.165
Wait a minute.
No.

22:13.083 --> 22:16.294
If you don't do it, I'll call the
police and tell them what I saw.

22:16.753 --> 22:17.754
What the fuck are you...

22:17.838 --> 22:18.839
His BMW.

22:19.548 --> 22:20.549
It's fixed.

22:21.842 --> 22:23.051
As if it had never happened.

22:25.053 --> 22:27.097
But I can't be fixed.

22:28.390 --> 22:29.933
He served three weeks.

22:30.475 --> 22:32.477
Three weeks for
what he did to me.

22:32.561 --> 22:35.647
Stupid judge, he sat there
and he looked at my face.

22:35.814 --> 22:36.857
I want it done.

22:36.940 --> 22:38.501
If you don't do it,
I'll call the police

22:38.525 --> 22:39.860
and I'll tell them what I saw.

22:41.027 --> 22:42.320
You'll do it!

22:42.571 --> 22:44.865
You want to save yourself?
Do it!

22:47.158 --> 22:48.159
Fuck.

22:53.915 --> 22:55.584
He didn't pay.
I understand.

22:55.667 --> 22:56.751
He didn't pay.

22:56.877 --> 22:58.077
Stop saying that!
I understand!

22:58.086 --> 22:59.045
Are you gonna do it?

22:59.129 --> 23:00.769
What I did, it has
nothing to do with you.

23:00.797 --> 23:01.882
You have to do this!

23:03.174 --> 23:04.426
He ruined my life.

23:04.718 --> 23:06.970
I have nothing.
I am nothing.

23:07.053 --> 23:08.805
I want it done
as soon as possible.

23:09.055 --> 23:10.473
Then I will forget.

23:10.640 --> 23:12.142
I will begin my life.

23:12.309 --> 23:14.019
And I will forget
that I ever met you.

23:14.102 --> 23:15.061
Do you know what it is
to kill a man?

23:15.145 --> 23:16.187
I will forget
that I ever met you.

23:16.271 --> 23:18.356
It's not a bug!
It's not a rat!

23:18.440 --> 23:19.900
I would never
kill a bug or a rat!

23:19.983 --> 23:21.401
He's much worse
than these things!

23:21.484 --> 23:22.903
You don't know what
you're getting into with me!

23:22.986 --> 23:24.404
You have no fucking idea!

23:24.988 --> 23:25.989
(PULLS HAND BREAK)

23:26.072 --> 23:27.073
(TIRES SQUEALING)

23:29.618 --> 23:30.785
(CARS HONKING)

23:32.078 --> 23:33.318
I could have called the police.

23:33.496 --> 23:34.956
I saved your life.

23:35.832 --> 23:37.918
Now you're gonna
give me back mine.

23:38.919 --> 23:41.838
If you're not going to kill me
you don't have a choice.

23:43.506 --> 23:44.674
(CAR TIRES SQUEALING)

23:45.842 --> 23:46.843
(CARS HONKING)

24:01.858 --> 24:02.901
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

24:02.984 --> 24:04.527
Back so soon?

24:12.243 --> 24:13.662
Beatrice.

24:16.623 --> 24:18.333
Beatrice,
tell me what went wrong.

24:18.500 --> 24:20.043
(FRENCH POP SONG PLAYING)

24:20.210 --> 24:21.211
Beatrice.

24:22.712 --> 24:24.589
(MUSIC CONTINUES
PLAYING LOUDLY)

25:20.061 --> 25:21.396
Ah, Laszlo.

25:21.479 --> 25:22.897
Sorry I'm late.
No problem.

25:23.064 --> 25:24.441
You look good.

25:25.650 --> 25:26.818
It's good to see you.

25:26.901 --> 25:28.821
Were you worried I was
going to forget your name?

25:28.945 --> 25:30.321
Ah...

25:31.239 --> 25:33.575
Convention.
You forget what it's like.

25:41.041 --> 25:42.792
(MEN CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY)

25:48.673 --> 25:51.051
It's Andras who gave us
the body for your grave.

25:52.635 --> 25:53.928
VICTOR: Whose body?

25:54.846 --> 25:56.806
Someone who
deserved it, I'm sure.

25:58.516 --> 25:59.559
(SPEAKING HUNGARIAN)

25:59.642 --> 26:01.561
Is this where
the whores are kept?

26:01.644 --> 26:02.645
(MAN LAUGHS)

26:03.271 --> 26:06.608
No, no, you are looking for
your mother's boat. Two down.

26:13.198 --> 26:14.199
We met.

26:15.867 --> 26:17.827
Two days after when
they left you for dead.

26:19.662 --> 26:20.663
VICTOR: Yeah.

26:23.750 --> 26:25.335
ANDRAS: Soviet modified
Dragunov.

26:25.502 --> 26:28.088
Shoots 7.62 by 5.4 rounds.

26:28.171 --> 26:31.633
With all Russian PSO scopes. Comes
with bayonet suppressor as well.

26:34.385 --> 26:35.845
Heavier than I expected.

26:36.679 --> 26:37.806
I'll take it.

26:39.099 --> 26:40.308
(MURMURING)

26:49.859 --> 26:50.860
Okay. All set.

26:55.698 --> 26:56.783
What did he say?

26:57.200 --> 26:58.201
Andras?

27:00.495 --> 27:03.998
For 14 months you've
infiltrated Alphonse.

27:05.166 --> 27:06.167
They wanted to know

27:06.251 --> 27:09.379
why you've been waiting for so
long to do what needs to be done.

27:10.171 --> 27:12.924
He said if he was lucky enough
to be standing, like you are,

27:13.508 --> 27:14.801
he'd want revenge, too.

27:15.176 --> 27:17.971
But we're all worried
you wait too long.

27:19.639 --> 27:23.143
Always kill the devil quickly when you find him.
That was his advice.

27:24.060 --> 27:27.522
I said you wanted to be close
enough to watch him suffer.

27:27.814 --> 27:31.234
But I really don't know
the reason you're waiting.

27:40.952 --> 27:42.871
VICTOR ON VIDEO: <i>So now...
Now.</i>

27:43.246 --> 27:44.789
VICTOR: <i>Say it
in English for me.</i>

27:45.123 --> 27:46.124
DELPHINE: <i>I...</i>

27:46.875 --> 27:48.126
MATILDE: <i>...tied...</i>
VICTOR: <i>Yes?</i>

27:48.334 --> 27:49.836
<i>I tied...</i>
VICTOR: <i>Yes?</i>

27:50.003 --> 27:52.505
<i>...my shoe. Today.</i>

27:53.464 --> 27:54.674
VICTOR: <i>You tied what?</i>

27:54.757 --> 27:56.176
DELPHINE: <i>My shoe.</i>

27:56.467 --> 27:58.595
<i>Your shoe?</i>
(MATILDE KISSING DELPHINE)

28:01.181 --> 28:03.942
VICTOR: <i>Bigger smile than that. That's
not the biggest smile you have.</i>

28:04.267 --> 28:05.685
(DAUGHTER GIGGLES)

28:25.788 --> 28:26.789
(MEN SPEAKING ALBANIAN)

28:26.873 --> 28:27.874
So?

28:27.957 --> 28:30.418
Nothing. No one
has seen your brother.

28:32.212 --> 28:33.880
It's been two weeks,
I am telling you.

28:33.963 --> 28:36.507
He never goes more than a few
days without calling me.

28:37.050 --> 28:39.260
You know him. Sometimes
he likes to get away.

28:39.761 --> 28:41.971
No. Something is wrong.

29:25.682 --> 29:27.308
What have I done to you?

29:27.725 --> 29:29.018
Where have you taken me?

29:31.688 --> 29:32.939
I need foodstuffs.

29:34.023 --> 29:35.858
(RATS SQUEALING)

29:53.876 --> 29:55.044
(GASPS)

29:59.549 --> 30:00.550
I can help you.

30:01.426 --> 30:03.219
If you let me go,
he will spare you.

30:04.137 --> 30:06.931
My brother, he will
not stop looking for me.

30:07.807 --> 30:09.600
And he will find you.

30:09.934 --> 30:11.477
(SOBBING)

30:14.480 --> 30:16.607
Even if you get his money,

30:16.733 --> 30:18.443
even if they pay,

30:18.818 --> 30:20.528
he will find you.

30:22.322 --> 30:23.865
(CAMERA CLICKING) (SOBS)

30:26.242 --> 30:28.870
You don't know who
you're messing with!

30:29.412 --> 30:31.080
He Will kill you!

30:31.622 --> 30:33.416
He Will kill you!

30:36.919 --> 30:38.421
(SOBBING)

30:38.713 --> 30:40.173
BOY 1: Monster's here.

30:40.256 --> 30:41.257
Monster!

30:41.966 --> 30:43.551
Hey, monster...

30:43.801 --> 30:46.512
If you put a bag over your head,
we might hook up with you.

30:46.596 --> 30:47.722
(ALL LAUGHING)

31:04.947 --> 31:07.116
You have to
take off your shoes.

31:07.200 --> 31:09.243
My mom likes to
keep the floor clean.

31:18.044 --> 31:19.284
BEATRICE: How long
will it take?

31:21.130 --> 31:22.211
Long enough to be prepared.

31:26.969 --> 31:29.305
You say he goes to
this bar every night?

31:30.973 --> 31:31.974
Yeah.

31:32.058 --> 31:34.060
You know where he works?

31:34.310 --> 31:36.145
He's looking for work.

31:36.437 --> 31:38.940
As much as I
could find out, I did.

31:49.158 --> 31:51.494
I never thought
about it before.

31:52.495 --> 31:53.746
Revenge.

31:58.751 --> 32:01.838
But when I saw you kill
that man in your apartment,

32:04.173 --> 32:06.092
I knew I had my answer.

32:14.308 --> 32:15.435
Why did you do it?

32:20.314 --> 32:22.525
I just want to
know more about you.

32:22.692 --> 32:24.610
I'm not here by choice.

32:31.534 --> 32:32.660
Oh!

32:33.035 --> 32:34.036
We have company.

32:34.120 --> 32:37.290
She can't hear us. She lost
most of her hearing as a child.

32:37.373 --> 32:38.374
(WOMEN SPEAKING FRENCH)

32:38.458 --> 32:40.585
Oh, I forgot my
cookies in the oven.

32:40.918 --> 32:42.462
I took them out for you, Mom.

32:43.671 --> 32:44.922
Oh, okay.

32:46.716 --> 32:49.051
I'm looking for
my hearing aids.

32:50.303 --> 32:52.889
Mom, I'd like you
to meet Victor.

32:53.556 --> 32:54.557
Oh!

32:54.724 --> 32:56.142
Hello, Victor.

32:56.225 --> 32:57.310
Nice to meet you.

32:57.393 --> 32:58.603
Nice to meet you.

32:58.728 --> 32:59.937
Well, you look good.

33:00.730 --> 33:01.898
You want to stay for lunch?

33:02.064 --> 33:04.484
We're having chicken. Lemon chicken.
It's very good.

33:04.567 --> 33:06.444
And cookies, too.

33:07.403 --> 33:08.946
We love cookies in this house.

33:09.363 --> 33:10.573
You want cookies?

33:10.740 --> 33:11.949
I can't stay, madame.

33:12.742 --> 33:14.911
Oh, I want to show
you something.

33:22.585 --> 33:24.712
Pictures of Beatrice.

33:26.088 --> 33:28.257
You can see she
has excellent genes.

33:30.009 --> 33:31.344
Isn't she pretty?

33:31.427 --> 33:33.638
You see how beautiful she is?

33:41.270 --> 33:42.438
Mmm.

33:50.613 --> 33:52.448
(VALENTINE CONTINUES
SPEAKING FRENCH)

34:03.084 --> 34:05.586
(VALENTINE EXCLAIMS
IN FRENCH)

34:09.090 --> 34:11.092
(VALENTINE HUMMING)

34:14.971 --> 34:17.056
I want it done as
soon as possible.

34:23.603 --> 34:25.188
<i>Maman?</i>
VALENTINE: Yes.

34:25.398 --> 34:26.399
Victor has to go.

34:31.862 --> 34:33.572
<i>Au revoir</i>, Victor.

34:34.156 --> 34:35.491
It was nice meeting you.

34:35.741 --> 34:37.034
Oh, I forgot...

34:39.495 --> 34:40.996
You'll hear from me
when it's done.

34:43.248 --> 34:44.625
Cookies.
Uh... (EXHALES)

34:44.833 --> 34:46.002
It's for you.
Take them.

34:51.340 --> 34:52.842
A bit grumpy.

34:54.719 --> 34:56.929
Him, I have
a good feeling about.

35:43.100 --> 35:44.435
Crackerjack.

35:44.518 --> 35:45.978
MAN: Got any grass?

35:47.438 --> 35:48.522
That depends.

35:51.817 --> 35:53.402
Information is power,
my friend.

35:53.736 --> 35:55.176
You see anyone
take a photo up there?

35:55.321 --> 35:56.447
Already told.

35:57.031 --> 35:58.240
Already told who?

35:58.574 --> 36:00.326
Another guy.
A guy like you.

36:01.535 --> 36:03.537
This is my friend Paul.

36:04.664 --> 36:05.706
Did you tell him?

36:11.045 --> 36:12.296
(RINGS)

36:15.216 --> 36:16.801
ALPHONSE: <i>Hello.</i>
GORDON: <i>It's Lon.</i>

36:17.259 --> 36:18.844
<i>You know,
people are flipping out.</i>

36:18.928 --> 36:20.554
<i>You weren't sanctioned
to do Harry.</i>

36:20.638 --> 36:23.015
<i>Or his men. Or leave a house
full of dead Jamaicans!</i>

36:24.141 --> 36:26.102
No, I told you...
<i>Can you try to imagine...</i>

36:26.185 --> 36:28.979
Look, Lon... <i>Imagine what
the fuck I'm dealing with?</i>

36:29.313 --> 36:30.793
<i>No. You need to
some see me right now.</i>

36:31.691 --> 36:34.068
<i>You don't appreciate
the severity of this.</i>

36:34.151 --> 36:36.946
<i>You come now.
I'm gonna be at Cafe Cora.</i>

36:57.883 --> 36:58.926
So...

37:00.636 --> 37:02.513
We got dead Jamaicans, huh?

37:04.140 --> 37:05.182
I'm listening.

37:08.269 --> 37:09.603
Well, Lon,

37:10.813 --> 37:14.191
for the last three months,
Harry was messing with me.

37:15.317 --> 37:16.652
Trying to freak me out.

37:17.027 --> 37:19.321
Sending little notes like this

37:19.905 --> 37:24.118
with pictures, and threats
and fucked-up shit.

37:28.080 --> 37:31.667
I don't think he was too happy
with the percentage deal.

37:32.001 --> 37:32.960
Okay.

37:33.043 --> 37:34.283
I went in there to get answers,

37:35.129 --> 37:36.839
not dead Jamaicans.

37:38.007 --> 37:39.008
Mmm-hmm.

37:39.675 --> 37:40.718
Turned out that way.

37:43.262 --> 37:44.847
I lost two guys.

37:45.222 --> 37:47.850
And truth is, I could have been
just as dead as both of them.

37:48.684 --> 37:50.770
You know Joe Bragg?
And Herbert?

37:51.896 --> 37:54.190
Lowell Khan.
And Weinberg?

37:55.191 --> 37:57.026
They're my colleagues.

37:57.860 --> 37:58.861
Yeah.

37:59.028 --> 38:00.154
Each

38:01.113 --> 38:02.990
received photos like these.

38:23.636 --> 38:25.179
(EARPIECE BUZZING)

38:26.806 --> 38:27.807
Yeah?

38:27.890 --> 38:29.225
DARCY ON PHONE: <i>Yo, Vic.
Where you at?</i>

38:29.308 --> 38:30.548
I'm in the middle of something.

38:30.726 --> 38:32.228
Hey, listen, I was right.

38:32.311 --> 38:33.432
Alphonse is still in danger.

38:33.479 --> 38:35.320
This was not Harry and
his men doing this shit.

38:37.316 --> 38:38.484
How do you know that?

38:38.567 --> 38:40.820
<i>You know Cafe Cora?
Can you get there?</i>

38:40.903 --> 38:42.071
I can find it.

38:42.196 --> 38:44.114
Yeah, look, Alphonse is
there with Lon Gordon.

38:44.281 --> 38:45.407
I'm gonna call
the rest of the crew

38:45.533 --> 38:46.659
and get them down there,
all right?

38:46.742 --> 38:47.743
How'd you know it wasn't Harry?

38:47.827 --> 38:48.869
I'll be there in five.

38:51.831 --> 38:52.915
Fuck.

38:54.375 --> 38:55.376
Yo, Terry.

38:55.960 --> 38:56.961
Yeah?

38:57.253 --> 38:58.933
I'm gonna look at
these photos another way.

38:59.755 --> 39:03.050
'Cause whoever's doing this is
taking it seriously enough now

39:03.133 --> 39:05.803
to let us know that the loans
to you, they're not secure.

39:06.303 --> 39:09.640
That's respect enough
to let us know his intentions.

39:11.934 --> 39:13.185
You're not gonna be around.

39:14.562 --> 39:15.563
You may not be
around to collect.

39:15.646 --> 39:17.898
Lon, that's exactly what
Harry wanted you to think.

39:17.982 --> 39:19.275
I got a note, too.

39:20.734 --> 39:22.194
This morning.

39:25.406 --> 39:26.824
It's addressed to you.

39:29.326 --> 39:32.371
Englishmen and Jamaicans, they
don't send notes like this.

39:33.664 --> 39:34.824
Not after they've been killed

39:35.457 --> 39:36.458
in their own house.

39:56.478 --> 39:58.147
What does it mean?

39:59.982 --> 40:01.233
What does it mean?

40:02.985 --> 40:05.946
And this key was taped to it.

40:11.994 --> 40:14.204
You know what that key is for?

40:20.044 --> 40:21.645
I want you to get
the books and the deeds

40:21.670 --> 40:23.422
together for me now, all right?

40:23.505 --> 40:25.716
Every building you owe us for.

40:28.052 --> 40:29.303
You understand this, don't you?

40:29.470 --> 40:31.847
So the uptown buildings, you're
pulling out of the deal?

40:31.931 --> 40:34.224
We're not
pulling out, Alphonse.

40:35.267 --> 40:37.311
You're just in no condition
right now to pull in.

40:44.485 --> 40:45.653
Shit!

41:05.214 --> 41:06.548
TERRY: Alphonse...
Not right now.

41:08.759 --> 41:10.427
TERRY: There's a problem.

41:10.970 --> 41:12.471
We need to go.

41:32.074 --> 41:33.200
(CELL PHONE CHIMES)

41:37.579 --> 41:38.914
He's here.
What?

41:39.289 --> 41:41.329
MAN 1: Oh, shit! MAN 2: Blotto's down.
Get the shit!

41:41.333 --> 41:42.334
TERRY: Jesus! Get down!

41:53.595 --> 41:55.806
Darcy! It's coming
from the roof!

41:56.640 --> 41:58.183
Get in the car!

41:58.934 --> 42:00.352
LUCO: Up there!

42:02.479 --> 42:03.647
(TIRES SQUEALING)

42:03.731 --> 42:04.732
ALPHONSE: Go, go, go!

42:08.777 --> 42:09.903
Get the fuck out of here!

42:10.029 --> 42:11.909
Luco! You watch the elevator!
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

42:11.947 --> 42:13.282
Dolph and Charles
come upstairs!

42:13.365 --> 42:14.950
Kilroy, back stairs
with me! Now!

42:49.902 --> 42:51.737
Darcy, he got out
from the fifth floor.

42:51.820 --> 42:53.489
What?
He went out the window!

42:54.573 --> 42:55.908
From the fifth fucking floor?

42:55.991 --> 42:57.576
He's crazy.

42:59.244 --> 43:00.444
(MEN GRUNTING ON PHONE) Darcy!

43:00.913 --> 43:01.914
(SCREAMS)

43:03.957 --> 43:06.919
What the fuck?
Shit! Fuck!

43:20.849 --> 43:21.850
Victor?

43:21.975 --> 43:22.976
(GRUNTS)

43:35.614 --> 43:36.615
Shit!

43:38.117 --> 43:39.201
Where is he?

43:39.284 --> 43:40.285
KILROY: They wasted Goff.

43:40.953 --> 43:42.204
DARCY: They wasted
Charles, too.

43:42.371 --> 43:43.622
Over here! Come on!

43:49.920 --> 43:51.130
(TIRES SCREECHING)

43:54.424 --> 43:55.509
Get in!

43:55.592 --> 43:56.593
Come on!

44:02.724 --> 44:04.059
MAN 1: Over here!

44:05.227 --> 44:06.562
MAN 2: Come on!

44:16.321 --> 44:18.448
What the fuck are you doing?

44:28.709 --> 44:31.211
Turn the fuck around!
Turn the fuck around!

44:35.007 --> 44:36.842
What the fuck!
Hi. I'm Beatrice.

44:36.925 --> 44:37.926
You told me to get here.

44:38.051 --> 44:39.636
I'm sorry I made him late.

44:39.720 --> 44:40.679
What's going on?

44:40.762 --> 44:41.763
See you later.

44:42.264 --> 44:43.891
DARCY: Did you see anyone
running here, Vic? No.

44:43.974 --> 44:44.975
Oh, shit!

44:45.100 --> 44:46.977
He took out Blotto, Goff
and even Charles. Who?

44:49.229 --> 44:50.314
KILROY: We lost him.

44:50.397 --> 44:51.440
Fuck!

44:51.732 --> 44:52.733
You guys all right?

44:56.445 --> 44:57.863
Tell him what you
told me about the cab.

44:57.946 --> 44:59.186
DARCY: This guy
in the building,

44:59.948 --> 45:02.659
he saw a man take this photo
from the stairwell.

45:02.743 --> 45:05.287
Then they see him get into a cab.
A gypsy cab.

45:05.370 --> 45:07.539
Paul was there, too.
He found out the same thing.

45:07.956 --> 45:10.396
It must've led him to something,
because he was wasted for it.

45:12.669 --> 45:13.921
Find out where the cab went.

45:19.968 --> 45:21.595
What did you do that for?

45:21.678 --> 45:22.721
What I do what for?

45:22.804 --> 45:23.964
Go looking with the pictures.

45:24.348 --> 45:26.475
You've only been on this crew
a month longer than I have.

45:26.558 --> 45:28.018
What if all this shit
that's happening to Alphonse

45:28.101 --> 45:30.896
is because of something that
went down before you came, huh?

45:32.231 --> 45:34.733
This is an opportunity of
magnumus proportions to me.

45:34.816 --> 45:36.068
How's that?

45:36.193 --> 45:37.444
Of finding my next step
in the organization.

45:37.819 --> 45:40.179
Yeah, well, there might not be
much of an organization left.

45:40.989 --> 45:43.283
I could run this place
for him, Victor.

45:43.367 --> 45:46.119
Better than Terry, a whole lot
better than fucking Kilroy.

45:46.536 --> 45:47.829
(SIRENS WAILING)

45:48.664 --> 45:50.499
I ain't joking around.

45:52.167 --> 45:53.418
If I could just
crack this shit for...

45:53.502 --> 45:54.670
This is serious shit, Darcy.

45:54.753 --> 45:57.089
Have enough money to buy Lise
and Theo what they need.

45:57.172 --> 45:58.298
Move up the ladder.

45:58.548 --> 45:59.675
What the fuck!

46:01.009 --> 46:02.261
It's Lise's car.
Mine's in the shop.

46:02.344 --> 46:03.425
What? Are you back
with her?

46:03.929 --> 46:06.056
Yeah, she's acknowledging me.

46:06.139 --> 46:07.182
It's a start, right?

46:07.849 --> 46:10.894
I promised her I'd
make a plan. Get ahead.

46:10.978 --> 46:13.105
For her and for Theo.

46:19.861 --> 46:21.863
Just don't get too smart.

46:22.447 --> 46:24.700
You saw what happened to Paul.

46:24.866 --> 46:25.993
I don't want anything
to happen to you.

46:26.076 --> 46:27.703
I'm smarter than Paul.

46:27.786 --> 46:29.587
I'm tired of being
taken for a fucking douche.

46:29.830 --> 46:32.165
I saw Alphonse respected me back there.
Oh, yeah?

46:32.249 --> 46:33.292
I saw it in his eyes.

46:34.293 --> 46:36.211
All right. We're good.
That's it.

46:59.568 --> 47:00.569
Go on.

47:01.320 --> 47:02.821
What the fuck.

47:13.749 --> 47:15.334
(DELPHINE GIGGLES
ON RECORDING)

47:16.585 --> 47:19.546
DELPHINE: <i>I tied
my shoe today.</i>

47:21.506 --> 47:23.550
(DELPHINE GIGGLES)

47:25.052 --> 47:28.221
<i>I tied my shoe today.</i>

47:30.265 --> 47:31.933
(DELPHINE GIGGLES)

47:33.977 --> 47:36.605
<i>I tied my shoe today.</i>

47:42.361 --> 47:43.362
(ANSWERS IN FRENCH)

47:43.695 --> 47:45.697
Hello. This is Victor,
is Beatrice...

47:46.948 --> 47:49.785
Hello. This is Victor.
Is Beatrice there?

47:50.744 --> 47:53.205
What? There's no answer,
no one is there.

47:53.288 --> 47:54.331
BEATRICE: Hello.

47:54.456 --> 47:55.665
It's me.

47:58.251 --> 48:00.170
<i>I believe you have
something of mine?</i>

48:00.253 --> 48:01.338
Yeah.

48:05.592 --> 48:07.469
Why did you follow me?

48:07.677 --> 48:09.638
<i>H's not the first time.</i>

48:10.847 --> 48:13.141
I wanted to find out
more about you.

48:19.189 --> 48:20.732
I think it's lucky I did.

48:20.816 --> 48:21.983
(DOORBELL RINGS)

48:53.682 --> 48:54.641
You want some water?

48:54.724 --> 48:55.725
Sure.

49:24.212 --> 49:25.797
BEATRICE: So, who are you?

49:37.976 --> 49:39.769
My real name is Laszlo Kerik.

49:42.189 --> 49:44.065
I was born in Hungary.

49:45.233 --> 49:48.195
A few years ago my wife
and I came to America.

49:50.822 --> 49:52.824
I was an engineer before.

49:54.868 --> 49:57.078
We came here looking for work.

49:58.872 --> 50:01.374
We took an apartment
in a building.

50:03.335 --> 50:05.420
It was a building
they wanted to control.

50:07.839 --> 50:08.965
The man I saw?

50:12.177 --> 50:14.095
They got most people
out of the building.

50:15.472 --> 50:19.309
One night they came
and they fired some shots.

50:20.268 --> 50:21.686
To scare us.

50:22.270 --> 50:23.939
So we would leave.

50:25.649 --> 50:27.859
A bullet went through a wall,

50:29.486 --> 50:32.405
and my daughter was
killed while she slept.

50:49.798 --> 50:52.634
We were going to testify.
My wife and I.

50:53.593 --> 50:56.680
The man responsible
for it all, Alphonse,

50:58.181 --> 51:01.726
he gave his orders to make
sure he never went to trial.

51:03.478 --> 51:04.813
And they were followed.

51:08.316 --> 51:10.360
He was afraid to
use his own guys,

51:10.443 --> 51:13.154
so they sent a crew
of Albanians after us.

51:14.948 --> 51:16.741
They killed my wife,

51:17.993 --> 51:20.495
and they thought
they killed me, too.

51:20.870 --> 51:23.498
And they should
have made sure of it.

51:31.590 --> 51:32.632
Cigarette?

51:33.925 --> 51:35.010
Yeah.

52:06.166 --> 52:09.085
When I manage to forget
what happened to me,

52:10.712 --> 52:14.424
when there are no mirrors,
and no people that reminds me,

52:16.217 --> 52:18.428
when my mom makes me laugh...

52:20.305 --> 52:21.806
In these moments,

52:22.307 --> 52:23.725
I have hope.

52:31.733 --> 52:33.610
<i>Maman</i> says that I...

52:34.986 --> 52:38.365
That it's these moments
that makes the pain bearable.

52:39.908 --> 52:41.409
These moments.

52:43.411 --> 52:47.791
I should try and find them where
I can and hang onto them.

52:50.335 --> 52:52.128
But they're fleeting.

52:52.629 --> 52:54.506
And then I remember,

52:54.589 --> 52:55.965
and I'm filled
with so much hate

52:57.300 --> 53:00.220
so I want to set
the whole world on fire.

53:06.518 --> 53:09.437
I'm sorry I made you tell me
about your family.

53:09.521 --> 53:12.273
I don't want to be one of those
people that reminds you.

53:12.524 --> 53:14.524
When you're the one who is
going to help me forget.

53:18.113 --> 53:21.616
These men, they don't
seem easy to beat.

53:22.617 --> 53:26.454
And you might have used
up all your luck. So...

53:34.504 --> 53:35.964
It's yellow...
Uh-uh.

53:36.131 --> 53:37.465
Chartreuse.

53:38.758 --> 53:39.968
Keep it.

53:41.010 --> 53:42.679
I need you around.

53:47.851 --> 53:50.270
Rabbits don't
come in chartreuse.

54:01.656 --> 54:02.741
Did you eat the cookies?

54:03.742 --> 54:04.784
No.

54:06.619 --> 54:08.121
Maman makes a good cookie.

54:11.750 --> 54:14.043
I only ask you to
return the Tupperware.

54:14.127 --> 54:16.129
She likes her Tupperware.

54:28.308 --> 54:30.393
Have you made any progress?

54:33.188 --> 54:34.355
I will.

54:34.814 --> 54:36.024
I know.

54:37.650 --> 54:41.404
Because I realize now that if I call
the police and tell them what I saw,

54:41.488 --> 54:43.865
it's not prison
you're afraid of.

